    "summary_one_sentence": "Two best-friend train stewardesses must team up with unlikely allies, including the US President, to stop a luxury express from crashing into Florida during a catastrophic storm.",
    "summary_short": "Tess and DeeDee are best friends and stewardesses who leave their dull jobs on the Stank Rail for the glamorous Glamazonian Express. When a massive Stormaganza threatens to derail the high-speed train into Celebration, Florida, the pair must act fast. They join forces with snobby first-class attendants, a handsome but dimwitted co-conductor, and President Judy Gagwell. Together, they work to save the train and everyone on board from disaster.",
    "summary_long": "Tess and DeeDee are best friends and train stewardesses tired of working dreary shifts on the Stank Rail line. Seeking excitement and glamour, they transfer to the prestigious Glamazonian Express, a high-speed luxury train. Onboard, they encounter snobby first-class attendants who look down on their coach-section background. During the journey, a catastrophic weather event called the Stormaganza strikes, damaging the train's controls and sending it on a collision course with Celebration, Florida. Realizing the danger, Tess and DeeDee step up to coordinate a rescue effort from the coach car. They recruit the reluctant first-class attendants, a hot but dimwitted co-conductor, and unexpectedly the fabulous US President Judy Gagwell, who happens to be a passenger. The group divides tasks to regain control, reroute power, and calm panicked passengers. Through comedic mishaps and brave actions, they manage to slow the train before impact. In the climax, President Gagwell helps them execute a daring maneuver that stops the express just in time. The friends celebrate their victory and newfound respect across class lines.",
    "synopsis": "Stop! That! Train! is an action-comedy-drama following best friends and stewardesses Tess and DeeDee as they trade mundane work on the Stank Rail for the dazzling Glamazonian Express. Their dream assignment turns perilous when a catastrophic Stormaganza puts the high-speed train on a crash course with Celebration, Florida. Forced to bridge the gap between coach and first class, the duo teams up with entitled first-class attendants, a charming yet clueless co-conductor, and the fabulous US President Judy Gagwell. Blending humor, heart, and high stakes, the film follows this mismatched group as they race against time to save the train and its passengers.",
